Class MessageList

  • Object
    • AbstractCollection<E>
      • AbstractList<E>
        • ArrayList<IMessage>
          • MessageList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IMessage, Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<IMessage>, Collection<IMessage>, List<IMessage>, RandomAccess

    public class MessageList
extends ArrayList<IMessage>
implements IMessage
    This class is a dummy IMessage that can host multiple messages.
    Usage:
     public IMessage produce(IMessage message, Connector.Interface out)
 {
      MessageList m = new MessageList();
      m.add(message.duplicate());
      m.add(message.duplicate());
      m.add(message.duplicate());
                return m; // <--- this is allowed !
 }

    Remember that you cannot create new IMessage yourself, you should call IMessage.duplicate() or ideally one of ConnectorHelper.copy() or ConnectorHelper.clean().
